types.name: remoteFile
types.description: Represents a remote file

properties.name: id
properties.description: Remote file identifier; may be empty. Can be used by the current user across application restarts or even from other devices. Uniquely identifies a file, but a file can have a lot of different valid identifiers. If the identifier starts with "http://" or "https://", it represents the HTTP URL of the file. TDLib is currently unable to download files if only their URL is known. If downloadFile/addFileToDownloads is called on such a file or if it is sent to a secret chat, TDLib starts a file generation process by sending updateFileGenerationStart to the application with the HTTP URL in the original_path and "#url#" as the conversion string. Application must generate the file by downloading it to the specified location

properties.name: unique_id
properties.description: Unique file identifier; may be empty if unknown. The unique file identifier which is the same for the same file even for different users and is persistent over time

properties.name: is_uploading_active
properties.description: True, if the file is currently being uploaded (or a remote copy is being generated by some other means)

properties.name: is_uploading_completed
properties.description: True, if a remote copy is fully available

properties.name: uploaded_size
properties.description: Size of the remote available part of the file, in bytes; 0 if unknown

types.description: Represents a secret chat

properties.description: Secret chat identifier

properties.name: user_id
properties.description: Identifier of the chat partner

properties.name: state
properties.description: State of the secret chat

properties.name: is_outbound
properties.description: True, if the chat was created by the current user; false otherwise

properties.name: key_hash
properties.description: Hash of the currently used key for comparison with the hash of the chat partner's key. This is a string of 36 little-endian bytes, which must be split into groups of 2 bits, each denoting a pixel of one of 4 colors FFFFFF, D5E6F3, 2D5775, and 2F99C9. The pixels must be used to make a 12x12 square image filled from left to right, top to bottom. Alternatively, the first 32 bytes of the hash can be converted to the hexadecimal format and printed as 32 2-digit hex numbers

properties.name: layer
properties.description: Secret chat layer; determines features supported by the chat partner's application. Nested text entities and underline and strikethrough entities are supported if the layer >= 101, files bigger than 2000MB are supported if the layer >= 143, spoiler and custom emoji text entities are supported if the layer >= 144

types.name: internalLinkTypeAttachmentMenuBot
types.description: The link is a link to an attachment menu bot to be opened in the specified or a chosen chat. Process given target_chat to open the chat. Then, call searchPublicChat with the given bot username, check that the user is a bot and can be added to attachment menu. Then, use getAttachmentMenuBot to receive information about the bot. If the bot isn't added to attachment menu, then show a disclaimer about Mini Apps being a third-party apps, ask the user to accept their Terms of service and confirm adding the bot to side and attachment menu. If the user accept the terms and confirms adding, then use toggleBotIsAddedToAttachmentMenu to add the bot. If the attachment menu bot can't be used in the opened chat, show an error to the user. If the bot is added to attachment menu and can be used in the chat, then use openWebApp with the given URL

properties.name: target_chat
properties.description: Target chat to be opened

properties.name: bot_username
properties.description: Username of the bot

properties.name: url
properties.description: URL to be passed to openWebApp

types.name: internalLinkTypeBotAddToChannel
types.description: The link is a link to a Telegram bot, which is supposed to be added to a channel chat as an administrator. Call searchPublicChat with the given bot username and check that the user is a bot, ask the current user to select a channel chat to add the bot to as an administrator. Then, call getChatMember to receive the current bot rights in the chat and if the bot already is an administrator, check that the current user can edit its administrator rights and combine received rights with the requested administrator rights. Then, show confirmation box to the user, and call setChatMemberStatus with the chosen chat and confirmed rights

properties.name: bot_username
properties.description: Username of the bot

properties.name: administrator_rights
properties.description: Expected administrator rights for the bot

types.name: internalLinkTypeBotStart
types.description: The link is a link to a chat with a Telegram bot. Call searchPublicChat with the given bot username, check that the user is a bot, show START button in the chat with the bot, and then call sendBotStartMessage with the given start parameter after the button is pressed

properties.name: bot_username

properties.name: start_parameter
properties.description: The parameter to be passed to sendBotStartMessage

properties.name: autostart
properties.description: True, if sendBotStartMessage must be called automatically without showing the START button

types.name: internalLinkTypeBotStartInGroup
types.description: The link is a link to a Telegram bot, which is supposed to be added to a group chat. Call searchPublicChat with the given bot username, check that the user is a bot and can be added to groups, ask the current user to select a basic group or a supergroup chat to add the bot to, taking into account that bots can be added to a public supergroup only by administrators of the supergroup. If administrator rights are provided by the link, call getChatMember to receive the current bot rights in the chat and if the bot already is an administrator, check that the current user can edit its administrator rights, combine received rights with the requested administrator rights, show confirmation box to the user, and call setChatMemberStatus with the chosen chat and confirmed administrator rights. Before call to setChatMemberStatus it may be required to upgrade the chosen basic group chat to a supergroup chat. Then, if start_parameter isn't empty, call sendBotStartMessage with the given start parameter and the chosen chat; otherwise, just send /start message with bot's username added to the chat.

properties.name: bot_username
properties.description: Username of the bot

properties.name: start_parameter
properties.description: The parameter to be passed to sendBotStartMessage

properties.name: administrator_rights
properties.description: Expected administrator rights for the bot; may be null

classes.name: TMeUrlType
classes.description: Describes the type of URL linking to an internal Telegram entity

classes.name: SuggestedAction
classes.description: Describes an action suggested to the current user

classes.name: TextParseMode
classes.description: Describes the way the text needs to be parsed for text entities

classes.name: ProxyType
classes.description: Describes the type of proxy server

classes.name: StatisticalGraph
classes.description: Describes a statistical graph

classes.name: ChatStatisticsObjectType
classes.description: Describes type of object, for which statistics are provided

classes.name: ChatStatistics
classes.description: Contains a detailed statistics about a chat

classes.name: RevenueWithdrawalState
classes.description: Describes state of a revenue withdrawal

classes.name: ChatRevenueTransactionType
classes.description: Describes type of transaction for revenue earned from sponsored messages in a chat

classes.name: VectorPathCommand
classes.description: Represents a vector path command

classes.name: BotCommandScope
classes.description: Represents the scope to which bot commands are relevant

classes.name: PhoneNumberCodeType
classes.description: Describes type of the request for which a code is sent to a phone number

classes.name: Update
classes.description: Contains notifications about data changes

classes.name: LogStream
classes.description: Describes a stream to which TDLib internal log is written

functions.name: getAuthorizationState
functions.description: Returns the current authorization state; this is an offline request. For informational purposes only. Use updateAuthorizationState instead to maintain the current authorization state. Can be called before initialization

functions.name: setTdlibParameters
functions.description: Sets the parameters for TDLib initialization. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitTdlibParameters

properties.name: use_test_dc
properties.description: Pass true to use Telegram test environment instead of the production environment

properties.name: database_directory
properties.description: The path to the directory for the persistent database; if empty, the current working directory will be used

properties.name: files_directory
properties.description: The path to the directory for storing files; if empty, database_directory will be used

properties.name: database_encryption_key
properties.description: Encryption key for the database. If the encryption key is invalid, then an error with code 401 will be returned

properties.name: use_file_database
properties.description: Pass true to keep information about downloaded and uploaded files between application restarts

properties.name: use_chat_info_database
properties.description: Pass true to keep cache of users, basic groups, supergroups, channels and secret chats between restarts. Implies use_file_database

properties.name: use_message_database
properties.description: Pass true to keep cache of chats and messages between restarts. Implies use_chat_info_database

properties.name: use_secret_chats
properties.description: Pass true to enable support for secret chats

properties.name: api_id
properties.description: Application identifier for Telegram API access, which can be obtained at https://my.telegram.org

properties.name: api_hash
properties.description: Application identifier hash for Telegram API access, which can be obtained at https://my.telegram.org

properties.name: system_language_code
properties.description: IETF language tag of the user's operating system language; must be non-empty

properties.name: device_model
properties.description: Model of the device the application is being run on; must be non-empty

properties.name: system_version
properties.description: Version of the operating system the application is being run on. If empty, the version is automatically detected by TDLib

properties.name: application_version
properties.description: Application version; must be non-empty

functions.name: setAuthenticationPhoneNumber
functions.description: Sets the phone number of the user and sends an authentication code to the user. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPhoneNumber, or if there is no pending authentication query and the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitEmailAddress, authorizationStateWaitEmailCode, authorizationStateWaitCode, authorizationStateWaitRegistration, or authorizationStateWaitPassword

properties.name: phone_number
properties.description: The phone number of the user, in international format

properties.name: settings
properties.description: Settings for the authentication of the user's phone number; pass null to use default settings

functions.name: setAuthenticationEmailAddress
functions.description: Sets the email address of the user and sends an authentication code to the email address. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitEmailAddress

properties.name: email_address
properties.description: The email address of the user

functions.name: resendAuthenticationCode
functions.description: Resends an authentication code to the user. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitCode, the next_code_type of the result is not null and the server-specified timeout has passed, or when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitEmailCode

properties.name: reason
properties.description: Reason of code resending; pass null if unknown

functions.name: checkAuthenticationEmailCode
functions.description: Checks the authentication of an email address. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitEmailCode

properties.name: code
properties.description: Email address authentication to check

functions.name: checkAuthenticationCode
functions.description: Checks the authentication code. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitCode

properties.name: code
properties.description: Authentication code to check

functions.name: requestQrCodeAuthentication
functions.description: Requests QR code authentication by scanning a QR code on another logged in device. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPhoneNumber, or if there is no pending authentication query and the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitEmailAddress, authorizationStateWaitEmailCode, authorizationStateWaitCode, authorizationStateWaitRegistration, or authorizationStateWaitPassword

properties.name: other_user_ids
properties.description: List of user identifiers of other users currently using the application

functions.name: registerUser
functions.description: Finishes user registration. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitRegistration

properties.name: first_name
properties.description: The first name of the user; 1-64 characters

properties.name: last_name
properties.description: The last name of the user; 0-64 characters

properties.name: disable_notification
properties.description: Pass true to disable notification about the current user joining Telegram for other users that added them to contact list

functions.name: resetAuthenticationEmailAddress
functions.description: Resets the login email address. May return an error with a message "TASK_ALREADY_EXISTS" if reset is still pending. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitEmailCode and authorization_state.can_reset_email_address == true

functions.name: checkAuthenticationPassword
functions.description: Checks the 2-step verification password for correctness. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPassword

properties.name: password
properties.description: The 2-step verification password to check

functions.name: requestAuthenticationPasswordRecovery
functions.description: Requests to send a 2-step verification password recovery code to an email address that was previously set up. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPassword

functions.name: checkAuthenticationPasswordRecoveryCode
functions.description: Checks whether a 2-step verification password recovery code sent to an email address is valid. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPassword

properties.name: recovery_code
properties.description: Recovery code to check

functions.name: recoverAuthenticationPassword
functions.description: Recovers the 2-step verification password with a password recovery code sent to an email address that was previously set up. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPassword

properties.name: recovery_code
properties.description: Recovery code to check

properties.name: new_password
properties.description: New 2-step verification password of the user; may be empty to remove the password

properties.name: new_hint
properties.description: New password hint; may be empty

functions.name: sendAuthenticationFirebaseSms
functions.description: Sends Firebase Authentication SMS to the phone number of the user. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitCode and the server returned code of the type authenticationCodeTypeFirebaseAndroid or authenticationCodeTypeFirebaseIos

properties.name: token
properties.description: Play Integrity API or SafetyNet Attestation API token for the Android application, or secret from push notification for the iOS application

functions.name: reportAuthenticationCodeMissing
functions.description: Reports that authentication code wasn't delivered via SMS; for official mobile applications only. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitCode

properties.name: mobile_network_code
properties.description: Current mobile network code

functions.name: checkAuthenticationBotToken
functions.description: Checks the authentication token of a bot; to log in as a bot. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPhoneNumber. Can be used instead of setAuthenticationPhoneNumber and checkAuthenticationCode to log in

properties.name: token
properties.description: The bot token

functions.name: logOut
functions.description: Closes the TDLib instance after a proper logout. Requires an available network connection. All local data will be destroyed. After the logout completes, updateAuthorizationState with authorizationStateClosed will be sent

functions.name: close
functions.description: Closes the TDLib instance. All databases will be flushed to disk and properly closed. After the close completes, updateAuthorizationState with authorizationStateClosed will be sent. Can be called before initialization

functions.name: destroy
functions.description: Closes the TDLib instance, destroying all local data without a proper logout. The current user session will remain in the list of all active sessions. All local data will be destroyed. After the destruction completes updateAuthorizationState with authorizationStateClosed will be sent. Can be called before authorization

functions.name: confirmQrCodeAuthentication
functions.description: Confirms QR code authentication on another device. Returns created session on success

properties.name: link
properties.description: A link from a QR code. The link must be scanned by the in-app camera

functions.name: getCurrentState
functions.description: Returns all updates needed to restore current TDLib state, i.e. all actual updateAuthorizationState/updateUser/updateNewChat and others. This is especially useful if TDLib is run in a separate process. Can be called before initialization

functions.name: setDatabaseEncryptionKey
functions.description: Changes the database encryption key. Usually the encryption key is never changed and is stored in some OS keychain

properties.name: new_encryption_key
properties.description: New encryption key

functions.name: getPasswordState
functions.description: Returns the current state of 2-step verification

functions.name: setPassword
functions.description: Changes the 2-step verification password for the current user. If a new recovery email address is specified, then the change will not be applied until the new recovery email address is confirmed

properties.name: old_password
properties.description: Previous 2-step verification password of the user

properties.name: new_password
properties.description: New 2-step verification password of the user; may be empty to remove the password

properties.name: new_hint
properties.description: New password hint; may be empty

properties.name: set_recovery_email_address
properties.description: Pass true to change also the recovery email address

properties.name: new_recovery_email_address
properties.description: New recovery email address; may be empty

functions.name: setLoginEmailAddress
functions.description: Changes the login email address of the user. The email address can be changed only if the current user already has login email and passwordState.login_email_address_pattern is non-empty. The change will not be applied until the new login email address is confirmed with checkLoginEmailAddressCode. To use Apple ID/Google ID instead of an email address, call checkLoginEmailAddressCode directly

properties.name: new_login_email_address
properties.description: New login email address

functions.name: resendLoginEmailAddressCode
functions.description: Resends the login email address verification code

functions.name: checkLoginEmailAddressCode
functions.description: Checks the login email address authentication

properties.name: code
properties.description: Email address authentication to check

functions.name: getRecoveryEmailAddress
functions.description: Returns a 2-step verification recovery email address that was previously set up. This method can be used to verify a password provided by the user

properties.name: password
properties.description: The 2-step verification password for the current user

functions.name: setRecoveryEmailAddress
functions.description: Changes the 2-step verification recovery email address of the user. If a new recovery email address is specified, then the change will not be applied until the new recovery email address is confirmed. If new_recovery_email_address is the same as the email address that is currently set up, this call succeeds immediately and aborts all other requests waiting for an email confirmation

properties.name: password
properties.description: The 2-step verification password of the current user

properties.name: new_recovery_email_address
properties.description: New recovery email address

functions.name: checkRecoveryEmailAddressCode
functions.description: Checks the 2-step verification recovery email address verification code

properties.name: code
properties.description: Verification code to check

functions.name: resendRecoveryEmailAddressCode
functions.description: Resends the 2-step verification recovery email address verification code

functions.name: cancelRecoveryEmailAddressVerification
functions.description: Cancels verification of the 2-step verification recovery email address

functions.name: requestPasswordRecovery
functions.description: Requests to send a 2-step verification password recovery code to an email address that was previously set up

functions.name: checkPasswordRecoveryCode
functions.description: Checks whether a 2-step verification password recovery code sent to an email address is valid

properties.name: recovery_code
properties.description: Recovery code to check

functions.name: recoverPassword
functions.description: Recovers the 2-step verification password using a recovery code sent to an email address that was previously set up

properties.name: recovery_code
properties.description: Recovery code to check

properties.name: new_password
properties.description: New 2-step verification password of the user; may be empty to remove the password

properties.name: new_hint
properties.description: New password hint; may be empty

functions.name: resetPassword
functions.description: Removes 2-step verification password without previous password and access to recovery email address. The password can't be reset immediately and the request needs to be repeated after the specified time

functions.name: cancelPasswordReset
functions.description: Cancels reset of 2-step verification password. The method can be called if passwordState.pending_reset_date > 0

functions.name: createTemporaryPassword
functions.description: Creates a new temporary password for processing payments

properties.name: password
properties.description: The 2-step verification password of the current user

properties.name: valid_for
properties.description: Time during which the temporary password will be valid, in seconds; must be between 60 and 86400

functions.name: getTemporaryPasswordState
functions.description: Returns information about the current temporary password

functions.name: getMe
functions.description: Returns the current user

functions.name: getUser
functions.description: Returns information about a user by their identifier. This is an offline request if the current user is not a bot

properties.name: user_id
properties.description: User identifier

functions.name: getUserFullInfo
functions.description: Returns full information about a user by their identifier

properties.name: user_id
properties.description: User identifier

functions.name: getBasicGroup
functions.description: Returns information about a basic group by its identifier. This is an offline request if the current user is not a bot

properties.name: basic_group_id
properties.description: Basic group identifier

functions.name: getBasicGroupFullInfo
functions.description: Returns full information about a basic group by its identifier

properties.name: basic_group_id
properties.description: Basic group identifier

functions.name: getSupergroup
functions.description: Returns information about a supergroup or a channel by its identifier. This is an offline request if the current user is not a bot

properties.name: supergroup_id
properties.description: Supergroup or channel identifier

functions.name: getSupergroupFullInfo
functions.description: Returns full information about a supergroup or a channel by its identifier, cached for up to 1 minute

properties.name: supergroup_id
properties.description: Supergroup or channel identifier

functions.name: getSecretChat
functions.description: Returns information about a secret chat by its identifier. This is an offline request

properties.name: secret_chat_id
properties.description: Secret chat identifier

functions.name: getChat
functions.description: Returns information about a chat by its identifier; this is an offline request if the current user is not a bot

properties.name: chat_id
properties.description: Chat identifier

functions.name: getMessage
functions.description: Returns information about a message

properties.name: chat_id
properties.description: Identifier of the chat the message belongs to

properties.name: message_id
properties.description: Identifier of the message to get

functions.name: getMessageLocally
functions.description: Returns information about a message, if it is available without sending network request. This is an offline request

properties.name: chat_id
properties.description: Identifier of the chat the message belongs to

properties.name: message_id
properties.description: Identifier of the message to get

functions.name: getRepliedMessage
functions.description: Returns information about a non-bundled message that is replied by a given message. Also, returns the pinned message, the game message, the invoice message, the message with a previously set same background, the giveaway message, and the topic creation message for messages of the types messagePinMessage, messageGameScore, messagePaymentSuccessful, messageChatSetBackground, messagePremiumGiveawayCompleted and topic messages without non-bundled replied message respectively

properties.name: chat_id
properties.description: Identifier of the chat the message belongs to

properties.name: message_id
properties.description: Identifier of the reply message

functions.name: getChatPinnedMessage
functions.description: Returns information about a newest pinned message in the chat

properties.name: chat_id
properties.description: Identifier of the chat the message belongs to

functions.name: getCallbackQueryMessage
functions.description: Returns information about a message with the callback button that originated a callback query; for bots only

properties.name: chat_id
properties.description: Identifier of the chat the message belongs to

properties.name: message_id
properties.description: Message identifier

properties.name: callback_query_id
properties.description: Identifier of the callback query

functions.name: getMessages
functions.description: Returns information about messages. If a message is not found, returns null on the corresponding position of the result

properties.name: chat_id
properties.description: Identifier of the chat the messages belong to

properties.name: message_ids
properties.description: Identifiers of the messages to get

functions.name: getMessageThread
functions.description: Returns information about a message thread. Can be used only if message.can_get_message_thread == true

properties.name: chat_id
properties.description: Chat identifier

properties.name: message_id
properties.description: Identifier of the message

functions.name: getMessageReadDate
functions.description: Returns read date of a recent outgoing message in a private chat. The method can be called if message.can_get_read_date == true and the message is read

properties.name: chat_id
properties.description: Chat identifier

properties.name: message_id
properties.description: Identifier of the message

functions.name: getMessageViewers
functions.description: Returns viewers of a recent outgoing message in a basic group or a supergroup chat. For video notes and voice notes only users, opened content of the message, are returned. The method can be called if message.can_get_viewers == true

properties.name: chat_id
properties.description: Chat identifier

properties.name: message_id
properties.description: Identifier of the message

functions.name: getFile
functions.description: Returns information about a file; this is an offline request

properties.name: file_id
properties.description: Identifier of the file to get

functions.name: getRemoteFile
functions.description: Returns information about a file by its remote identifier; this is an offline request. Can be used to register a URL as a file for further uploading, or sending as a message. Even the request succeeds, the file can be used only if it is still accessible to the user. For example, if the file is from a message, then the message must be not deleted and accessible to the user. If the file database is disabled, then the corresponding object with the file must be preloaded by the application

properties.name: remote_file_id
properties.description: Remote identifier of the file to get

properties.name: file_type
properties.description: File type; pass null if unknown

functions.name: loadChats
functions.description: Loads more chats from a chat list. The loaded chats and their positions in the chat list will be sent through updates. Chats are sorted by the pair (chat.position.order, chat.id) in descending order. Returns a 404 error if all chats have been loaded

properties.name: chat_list
properties.description: The chat list in which to load chats; pass null to load chats from the main chat list

properties.name: limit
properties.description: The maximum number of chats to be loaded. For optimal performance, the number of loaded chats is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit, even if the end of the list is not reached

functions.name: getChats
functions.description: Returns an ordered list of chats from the beginning of a chat list. For informational purposes only. Use loadChats and updates processing instead to maintain chat lists in a consistent state

properties.name: chat_list
properties.description: The chat list in which to return chats; pass null to get chats from the main chat list

properties.name: limit
properties.description: The maximum number of chats to be returned

functions.name: searchPublicChat
functions.description: Searches a public chat by its username. Currently, only private chats, supergroups and channels can be public. Returns the chat if found; otherwise, an error is returned

properties.name: username
properties.description: Username to be resolved

functions.name: searchPublicChats
functions.description: Searches public chats by looking for specified query in their username and title. Currently, only private chats, supergroups and channels can be public. Returns a meaningful number of results. Excludes private chats with contacts and chats from the chat list from the results

properties.name: query
properties.description: Query to search for

functions.name: searchChats
functions.description: Searches for the specified query in the title and username of already known chats; this is an offline request. Returns chats in the order seen in the main chat list

properties.name: query
properties.description: Query to search for. If the query is empty, returns up to 50 recently found chats

properties.name: limit
properties.description: The maximum number of chats to be returned

functions.name: searchChatsOnServer
functions.description: Searches for the specified query in the title and username of already known chats via request to the server. Returns chats in the order seen in the main chat list

properties.name: query
properties.description: Query to search for

properties.name: limit
properties.description: The maximum number of chats to be returned

functions.name: searchChatsNearby
functions.description: Returns a list of users and location-based supergroups nearby. The list of users nearby will be updated for 60 seconds after the request by the updates updateUsersNearby. The request must be sent again every 25 seconds with adjusted location to not miss new chats

properties.name: location
properties.description: Current user location

functions.name: getRecommendedChats
functions.description: Returns a list of channel chats recommended to the current user

functions.name: getChatSimilarChats
functions.description: Returns a list of chats similar to the given chat

properties.name: chat_id
properties.description: Identifier of the target chat; must be an identifier of a channel chat

functions.name: getChatSimilarChatCount
functions.description: Returns approximate number of chats similar to the given chat

properties.name: chat_id
properties.description: Identifier of the target chat; must be an identifier of a channel chat

properties.name: return_local
properties.description: Pass true to get the number of chats without sending network requests, or -1 if the number of chats is unknown locally

functions.name: openChatSimilarChat
functions.description: Informs TDLib that a chat was opened from the list of similar chats. The method is independent of openChat and closeChat methods

properties.name: chat_id
properties.description: Identifier of the original chat, which similar chats were requested

properties.name: opened_chat_id
properties.description: Identifier of the opened chat

functions.name: getTopChats
functions.description: Returns a list of frequently used chats

properties.name: category
properties.description: Category of chats to be returned

properties.name: limit
properties.description: The maximum number of chats to be returned; up to 30

functions.name: removeTopChat
functions.description: Removes a chat from the list of frequently used chats. Supported only if the chat info database is enabled

properties.name: category
properties.description: Category of frequently used chats

properties.name: chat_id
properties.description: Chat identifier

functions.name: searchRecentlyFoundChats
functions.description: Searches for the specified query in the title and username of up to 50 recently found chats; this is an offline request

properties.name: query
properties.description: Query to search for

properties.name: limit
properties.description: The maximum number of chats to be returned

functions.name: addRecentlyFoundChat
functions.description: Adds a chat to the list of recently found chats. The chat is added to the beginning of the list. If the chat is already in the list, it will be removed from the list first

properties.name: chat_id
properties.description: Identifier of the chat to add

functions.name: removeRecentlyFoundChat
functions.description: Removes a chat from the list of recently found chats

properties.name: chat_id
properties.description: Identifier of the chat to be removed

functions.name: clearRecentlyFoundChats
functions.description: Clears the list of recently found chats

functions.name: getRecentlyOpenedChats
functions.description: Returns recently opened chats; this is an offline request. Returns chats in the order of last opening

properties.name: limit
properties.description: The maximum number of chats to be returned

functions.name: checkChatUsername
functions.description: Checks whether a username can be set for a chat

properties.name: chat_id
properties.description: Chat identifier; must be identifier of a supergroup chat, or a channel chat, or a private chat with self, or 0 if the chat is being created

properties.name: username
properties.description: Username to be checked

functions.name: getCreatedPublicChats
functions.description: Returns a list of public chats of the specified type, owned by the user

properties.name: type
properties.description: Type of the public chats to return

functions.name: checkCreatedPublicChatsLimit
functions.description: Checks whether the maximum number of owned public chats has been reached. Returns corresponding error if the limit was reached. The limit can be increased with Telegram Premium

properties.name: type
properties.description: Type of the public chats, for which to check the limit

functions.name: getSuitableDiscussionChats
functions.description: Returns a list of basic group and supergroup chats, which can be used as a discussion group for a channel. Returned basic group chats must be first upgraded to supergroups before they can be set as a discussion group. To set a returned supergroup as a discussion group, access to its old messages must be enabled using toggleSupergroupIsAllHistoryAvailable first

functions.name: getInactiveSupergroupChats
functions.description: Returns a list of recently inactive supergroups and channels. Can be used when user reaches limit on the number of joined supergroups and channels and receives CHANNELS_TOO_MUCH error. Also, the limit can be increased with Telegram Premium

functions.name: getSuitablePersonalChats
functions.description: Returns a list of channel chats, which can be used as a personal chat

functions.name: loadSavedMessagesTopics
functions.description: Loads more Saved Messages topics. The loaded topics will be sent through updateSavedMessagesTopic. Topics are sorted by their topic.order in descending order. Returns a 404 error if all topics have been loaded

properties.name: limit
properties.description: The maximum number of topics to be loaded. For optimal performance, the number of loaded topics is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit, even if the end of the list is not reached

functions.name: getSavedMessagesTopicHistory
functions.description: Returns messages in a Saved Messages topic. The messages are returned in a reverse chronological order (i.e., in order of decreasing message_id)

properties.name: saved_messages_topic_id
properties.description: Identifier of Saved Messages topic which messages will be fetched

properties.name: from_message_id
properties.description: Identifier of the message starting from which messages must be fetched; use 0 to get results from the last message

properties.name: offset
properties.description: Specify 0 to get results from exactly the message from_message_id or a negative offset up to 99 to get additionally some newer messages

properties.name: limit
properties.description: The maximum number of messages to be returned; must be positive and can't be greater than 100. If the offset is negative, the limit must be greater than or equal to -offset. For optimal performance, the number of returned messages is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

functions.name: getSavedMessagesTopicMessageByDate
functions.description: Returns the last message sent in a Saved Messages topic no later than the specified date

properties.name: saved_messages_topic_id
properties.description: Identifier of Saved Messages topic which message will be returned

properties.name: date
properties.description: Point in time (Unix timestamp) relative to which to search for messages

functions.name: deleteSavedMessagesTopicHistory
functions.description: Deletes all messages in a Saved Messages topic

properties.name: saved_messages_topic_id
properties.description: Identifier of Saved Messages topic which messages will be deleted

functions.name: deleteSavedMessagesTopicMessagesByDate
functions.description: Deletes all messages between the specified dates in a Saved Messages topic. Messages sent in the last 30 seconds will not be deleted

properties.name: saved_messages_topic_id
properties.description: Identifier of Saved Messages topic which messages will be deleted

properties.name: min_date
properties.description: The minimum date of the messages to delete

properties.name: max_date
properties.description: The maximum date of the messages to delete

functions.name: toggleSavedMessagesTopicIsPinned
functions.description: Changes the pinned state of a Saved Messages topic. There can be up to getOption("pinned_saved_messages_topic_count_max") pinned topics. The limit can be increased with Telegram Premium

properties.name: saved_messages_topic_id
properties.description: Identifier of Saved Messages topic to pin or unpin

properties.name: is_pinned
properties.description: Pass true to pin the topic; pass false to unpin it

functions.name: setPinnedSavedMessagesTopics
functions.description: Changes the order of pinned Saved Messages topics

properties.name: saved_messages_topic_ids
properties.description: Identifiers of the new pinned Saved Messages topics

functions.name: getGroupsInCommon
functions.description: Returns a list of common group chats with a given user. Chats are sorted by their type and creation date

properties.name: user_id
properties.description: User identifier

properties.name: offset_chat_id
properties.description: Chat identifier starting from which to return chats; use 0 for the first request

properties.name: limit
properties.description: The maximum number of chats to be returned; up to 100

functions.name: getChatHistory
functions.description: Returns messages in a chat. The messages are returned in a reverse chronological order (i.e., in order of decreasing message_id). For optimal performance, the number of returned messages is chosen by TDLib. This is an offline request if only_local is true

properties.name: chat_id
properties.description: Chat identifier

properties.name: from_message_id
properties.description: Identifier of the message starting from which history must be fetched; use 0 to get results from the last message

properties.name: offset
properties.description: Specify 0 to get results from exactly the message from_message_id or a negative offset up to 99 to get additionally some newer messages

properties.name: limit

properties.name: chat_id

properties.description: New time relative to the message send date, for which the location can be updated, in seconds. If 0x7FFFFFFF specified, then the location can be updated forever. The shortcut must not contain more than getOption("quick_reply_shortcut_message_count_max") messages after adding the new message. Returns the added message

functions.description: Readds quick reply messages which failed to add. If a message is readded, the corresponding failed to send message is deleted. Returns the sent messages in the same order as the message identifiers passed in message_ids. If a message can't be readded, null will be returned instead of the message

properties.name: shortcut_name
properties.description: Name of the target shortcut

properties.name: message_ids
properties.description: Identifiers of the quick reply messages to readd. Message identifiers must be in a strictly increasing order

properties.description: New content of the message. Must be one of the following types: inputMessageText, inputMessageAnimation, inputMessageAudio, inputMessageDocument, inputMessagePhoto or inputMessageVideo

properties.name: offset

functions.name: downloadFile
functions.description: Downloads a file from the cloud. Download progress and completion of the download will be notified through updateFile updates

properties.name: file_id
properties.description: Identifier of the file to download

properties.name: priority
properties.description: Priority of the download (1-32). The higher the priority, the earlier the file will be downloaded. If the priorities of two files are equal, then the last one for which downloadFile/addFileToDownloads was called will be downloaded first

properties.name: offset
properties.description: The starting position from which the file needs to be downloaded

properties.name: limit
properties.description: Number of bytes which need to be downloaded starting from the "offset" position before the download will automatically be canceled; use 0 to download without a limit

properties.name: synchronous
properties.description: Pass true to return response only after the file download has succeeded, has failed, has been canceled, or a new downloadFile request with different offset/limit parameters was sent; pass false to return file state immediately, just after the download has been started

functions.name: getFileDownloadedPrefixSize
functions.description: Returns file downloaded prefix size from a given offset, in bytes

properties.name: file_id
properties.description: Identifier of the file

properties.name: offset
properties.description: Offset from which downloaded prefix size needs to be calculated

functions.name: cancelDownloadFile
functions.description: Stops the downloading of a file. If a file has already been downloaded, does nothing

properties.name: file_id
properties.description: Identifier of a file to stop downloading

properties.name: only_if_pending
properties.description: Pass true to stop downloading only if it hasn't been started, i.e. request hasn't been sent to server

functions.name: getSuggestedFileName
functions.description: Returns suggested name for saving a file in a given directory

properties.name: file_id
properties.description: Identifier of the file

properties.name: directory
properties.description: Directory in which the file is supposed to be saved

functions.name: preliminaryUploadFile
functions.description: Preliminary uploads a file to the cloud before sending it in a message, which can be useful for uploading of being recorded voice and video notes. In all other cases there is no need to preliminary upload a file. Updates updateFile will be used to notify about upload progress. The upload will not be completed until the file is sent in a message

properties.name: file
properties.description: File to upload

properties.name: file_type
properties.description: File type; pass null if unknown

properties.name: priority
properties.description: Priority of the upload (1-32). The higher the priority, the earlier the file will be uploaded. If the priorities of two files are equal, then the first one for which preliminaryUploadFile was called will be uploaded first

functions.name: cancelPreliminaryUploadFile
functions.description: Stops the preliminary uploading of a file. Supported only for files uploaded by using preliminaryUploadFile. For other files the behavior is undefined

properties.name: file_id
properties.description: Identifier of the file to stop uploading

functions.name: writeGeneratedFilePart
functions.description: Writes a part of a generated file. This method is intended to be used only if the application has no direct access to TDLib's file system, because it is usually slower than a direct write to the destination file

properties.name: generation_id
properties.description: The identifier of the generation process

properties.name: offset
properties.description: The offset from which to write the data to the file

properties.name: data
properties.description: The data to write

functions.name: setFileGenerationProgress
functions.description: Informs TDLib on a file generation progress

properties.name: generation_id
properties.description: The identifier of the generation process

properties.name: expected_size
properties.description: Expected size of the generated file, in bytes; 0 if unknown

properties.name: local_prefix_size
properties.description: The number of bytes already generated

functions.name: finishFileGeneration
functions.description: Finishes the file generation

properties.name: generation_id
properties.description: The identifier of the generation process

properties.name: error
properties.description: If passed, the file generation has failed and must be terminated; pass null if the file generation succeeded

functions.name: readFilePart
functions.description: Reads a part of a file from the TDLib file cache and returns read bytes. This method is intended to be used only if the application has no direct access to TDLib's file system, because it is usually slower than a direct read from the file

properties.name: file_id
properties.description: Identifier of the file. The file must be located in the TDLib file cache

properties.name: offset
properties.description: The offset from which to read the file

properties.name: count
properties.description: Number of bytes to read. An error will be returned if there are not enough bytes available in the file from the specified position. Pass 0 to read all available data from the specified position

functions.name: deleteFile
functions.description: Deletes a file from the TDLib file cache

properties.name: file_id
properties.description: Identifier of the file to delete

functions.name: addFileToDownloads
functions.description: Adds a file from a message to the list of file downloads. Download progress and completion of the download will be notified through updateFile updates. If message database is used, the list of file downloads is persistent across application restarts. The downloading is independent of download using downloadFile, i.e. it continues if downloadFile is canceled or is used to download a part of the file

properties.name: file_id
properties.description: Identifier of the file to download

properties.name: chat_id
properties.description: Chat identifier of the message with the file

properties.name: message_id
properties.description: Message identifier

properties.name: priority
properties.description: Priority of the download (1-32). The higher the priority, the earlier the file will be downloaded. If the priorities of two files are equal, then the last one for which downloadFile/addFileToDownloads was called will be downloaded first

functions.name: toggleDownloadIsPaused
functions.description: Changes pause state of a file in the file download list

properties.name: file_id
properties.description: Identifier of the downloaded file

properties.name: is_paused
properties.description: Pass true if the download is paused

functions.name: toggleAllDownloadsArePaused
functions.description: Changes pause state of all files in the file download list

properties.name: are_paused
properties.description: Pass true to pause all downloads; pass false to unpause them

functions.name: removeFileFromDownloads

properties.name: file_id

properties.name: delete_from_cache

functions.name: removeAllFilesFromDownloads

properties.name: only_active

properties.name: only_completed

properties.name: delete_from_cache

properties.name: only_completed

properties.name: offset
properties.description: Offset of the first entry to return as received from the previous request; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

properties.name: limit
properties.description: The maximum number of files to be returned

Value 0 corresponds to fatal errors, value 1 corresponds to errors, value 2 corresponds to warnings and debug warnings, value 3 corresponds to informational, value 4 corresponds to debug, value 5 corresponds to verbose debug, value greater than 5 and up to 1023 can be used to enable even more logging
